  "term": "def:oscillation-on-a-set",
  "kind": "Definition",
  "title": "Oscillation on a Set",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $A\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}$, let $f:A\\to\\mathbb{R}$, and let\n$E\\subseteq A$. The oscillation of $f$ on $E$ is the extended real number\n\\[\n\\omega(f;E)\\coloneqq\n\\sup\\{\\,|f(x_1)-f(x_2)|:x_1,x_2\\in E\\,\\}\n=\\mathrm{diam}(f(E)).\n\\]",
